util

Class Vector2D

  • java.lang.Object
    • util.Vector2D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Vector2D>

    public class Vector2D
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Vector2D>, java.io.Serializable
    Class for all 2d-vector calculations. This class is non-modifying, meaning that a.add(b) does not change a but only returns the sum. To add b to a you should therefore use a = a.add(b) or a = Vector2D.add(a,b). This means that a.add(b).add(c).add(d) returns a+b+c+d and modifies none of them. To normalize a vector you therefore need to use a = a.normalize(). All internal calculations are done with double precision.
    Version:
    2016-03-04
    Author:
    Gustav
